================================================================================
CHIP-8 EMULATOR v1.0
================================================================================

LANGUAGE : C
PLATFORM : macOS / Linux / Windows (with SDL2)

================================================================================
DESCRIPTION
================================================================================

This is a CHIP-8 interpreter/emulator written in C. CHIP-8 is an interpreted
programming language developed in the mid-1970s. It was made to allow video
games to be more easily programmed for 8-bit microcomputers.

The emulator implements the full CHIP-8 instruction set and features:

    * 4KB RAM
    * 16 8-bit registers (V0-VF)
    * 16-level stack
    * 64x32 pixel monochrome display
    * 16-key hexadecimal keypad
    * Delay and sound timers
    * 35 opcodes

================================================================================
REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

    * C compiler (gcc, clang, etc.)
    * SDL2 library for graphics and input

================================================================================
COMPILATION
================================================================================

On macOS/Linux:

    $ gcc -o chip8 main.c chip8.c -lSDL2

On Linux (alternative):

    $ gcc -o chip8 main.c chip8.c `sdl2-config --cflags --libs`

================================================================================
CONTROLS
================================================================================

CHIP-8 uses a 16-key hexadecimal keypad with the following layout:

    Original CHIP-8 Keypad:        This Emulator Mapping:

         1 2 3 C                        1 2 3 4
         4 5 6 D                        Q W E R
         7 8 9 E                        A S D F
         A 0 B F                        Z X C V

================================================================================
FILE STRUCTURE
================================================================================

    chip8.h         - Header file with structure definitions
    chip8.c         - Core emulator implementation (opcodes, CPU)
    main.c          - SDL2 frontend and main loop
    README          - This file

================================================================================
NOTES
================================================================================

- ROMs should be placed in the same directory as the executable
- Display refreshes at 60Hz
- Timers count down at 60Hz
- The interpreter space (0x000-0x1FF) contains the font set
- Programs start at memory address 0x200

=========================================================================

